$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$2"}}],["$","$L3",null,{}],["$","$L4",null,{}],["$","article",null,{"className":"pt-28 md:pt-36 pb-20 max-w-[740px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-12","children":[["$","nav",null,{"aria-label":"Breadcrumb","className":"mb-8","children":["$","ol",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-xs text-muted","children":[["$","li",null,{"children":["$","$L5",null,{"href":"/","className":"hover:text-dark transition-colors","children":"Home"}]}],["$","li",null,{"children":"/"}],["$","li",null,{"children":["$","$L5",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"hover:text-dark transition-colors","children":"Blog"}]}],["$","li",null,{"children":"/"}],["$","li",null,{"className":"text-dark truncate max-w-[200px]","children":"API Integration Best Practices: Building Reliable Data Flows Between Systems"}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-4","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs font-mono text-coral uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Engineering"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-muted","children":"24 January 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-muted","children":"9 min read"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"font-serif text-dark leading-[1.15] mb-6","style":{"fontSize":"clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem)"},"children":"API Integration Best Practices: Building Reliable Data Flows Between Systems"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg text-gray-500 mb-10 leading-relaxed font-sans","children":"APIs are how modern systems talk to each other. Learn best practices for building reliable, maintainable integrations that do not break when the other side changes."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"border-t border-[#EEEEEE] mb-10"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-10","children":[["$","span","API",{"className":"text-xs font-mono bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 rounded-full px-3 py-1","children":"API"}],["$","span","integration",{"className":"text-xs font-mono bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 rounded-full px-3 py-1","children":"integration"}],["$","span","backend development",{"className":"text-xs font-mono bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 rounded-full px-3 py-1","children":"backend development"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose-goated","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Every modern business uses multiple software systems. Your CRM talks to your email platform. Your e-commerce system talks to your inventory management system. Your accounting software talks to your payment processor."}]]}],["$","p","1",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"These systems communicate through APIs. And most of these integrations are fragile, break frequently, and sync data incorrectly."}]]}],["$","p","2",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"We have debugged hundreds of broken integrations. Here is what actually works."}]]}],["$","h2","3",{"className":"font-serif text-2xl text-dark mt-12 mb-4","children":"The Problem With Most Integrations"}],["$","h3","4",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"They are too tightly coupled"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"The integration assumes the other system will never change. When it does, everything breaks."}]]}],["$","h3","6",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"They do not handle failures gracefully"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"If the API is temporarily down, the entire workflow fails. No retry logic, no queue, no fallback."}]]}],["$","h3","8",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"They duplicate data instead of syncing it"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Data flows in one direction and never updates. Your CRM has customer data that conflicts with your accounting system."}]]}],["$","h3","10",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"They lack visibility"}],["$","p","11",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"When something breaks, you have no idea it is broken until customers complain."}]]}],["$","h2","12",{"className":"font-serif text-2xl text-dark mt-12 mb-4","children":"The Architecture That Works"}],["$","h3","13",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"Use Event-Driven Architecture"}],["$","p","14",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Instead of calling the API directly and waiting for a response, publish an event. A background worker processes the event and calls the API. If the API fails, the event stays in the queue and retries automatically."}]]}],["$","p","15",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Benefits: Decouples systems, handles failures gracefully, scales to high volume."}]]}],["$","h3","16",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"Implement Retry Logic"}],["$","p","17",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"API calls fail. Temporarily. Implement exponential backoff: retry immediately, then after 1 second, 5 seconds, 30 seconds, 5 minutes. By the 5th retry, a temporary outage has likely resolved."}]]}],["$","h3","18",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"Use Webhooks Instead of Polling"}],["$","p","19",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Instead of your system asking \"is there new data?\" every 5 minutes, have the other system tell you when something changes via a webhook. Faster, more efficient, more reliable."}]]}],["$","h3","20",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"Maintain an Audit Trail"}],["$","p","21",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Log every API call: what was sent, what was received, whether it succeeded. When something goes wrong, you can see the full history."}]]}],["$","h3","22",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"Implement Idempotency"}],["$","p","23",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"If the same API call is processed twice, it should have the same effect as being processed once. This prevents duplicate data, duplicate charges, and other nightmares."}]]}],["$","h2","24",{"className":"font-serif text-2xl text-dark mt-12 mb-4","children":"The Tech Stack"}],["$","h3","25",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"Message Queues"}],["$","p","26",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"RabbitMQ, Kafka, or AWS SQS. Pick the message queue that scales to your volume."}]]}],["$","h3","27",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"Worker Processes"}],["$","p","28",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Run background workers that consume from the queue and process API calls. If a worker crashes, the message stays in the queue."}]]}],["$","h3","29",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"Monitoring and Alerting"}],["$","p","30",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Monitor API response times, error rates, and queue depth. Alert when something goes wrong."}]]}],["$","h3","31",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"API Documentation"}],["$","p","32",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Document your API clearly with examples. Many integration problems stem from misunderstanding what the API actually does."}]]}],["$","h2","33",{"className":"font-serif text-2xl text-dark mt-12 mb-4","children":"Common Integration Patterns"}],["$","h3","34",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"Bidirectional Sync"}],["$","p","35",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Data flows both directions. Customer updates in your CRM should sync to your email platform, and vice versa."}]]}],["$","p","36",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":""}],["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-semibold text-dark","children":"Challenge:"}],["$","span","2",{"children":" Handling conflicts when both systems change the same data."}]]}],["$","p","37",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":""}],["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-semibold text-dark","children":"Solution:"}],["$","span","2",{"children":" Use timestamps. The most recent change wins. Or detect conflicts and escalate to humans."}]]}],["$","h3","38",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"Event-Triggered Actions"}],["$","p","39",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"When X happens in system A, do Y in system B."}]]}],["$","p","40",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":""}],["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-semibold text-dark","children":"Example:"}],["$","span","2",{"children":" When a customer makes a purchase in Shopify, automatically create a customer record in Salesforce, send them a welcome email, and generate an invoice."}]]}],["$","p","41",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":""}],["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-semibold text-dark","children":"Challenge:"}],["$","span","2",{"children":" Coordinating multiple downstream actions. If step 2 fails, do we retry step 2 or the entire flow?"}]]}],["$","p","42",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":""}],["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-semibold text-dark","children":"Solution:"}],["$","span","2",{"children":" Break into independent atomic operations. If an operation fails, retry just that operation."}]]}],["$","h3","43",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"Scheduled Syncs"}],["$","p","44",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Every night at 2am, sync data between systems."}]]}],["$","p","45",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":""}],["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-semibold text-dark","children":"Challenge:"}],["$","span","2",{"children":" If sync fails, you do not notice until the next morning."}]]}],["$","p","46",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":""}],["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-semibold text-dark","children":"Solution:"}],["$","span","2",{"children":" Monitor sync success. Alert if sync takes longer than usual or fails."}]]}],["$","h2","47",{"className":"font-serif text-2xl text-dark mt-12 mb-4","children":"Real Example: CRM to Email Platform Integration"}],["$","p","48",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":""}],["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-semibold text-dark","children":"Requirements:"}],["$","span","2",{"children":""}]]}],["$","li","49",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Customer added to CRM → automatically subscribe to email list"}]]}],["$","li","50",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Customer updates email in CRM → update email platform"}]]}],["$","li","51",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Customer marked as \"lost\" in CRM → unsubscribe from email platform"}]]}],["$","li","52",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Email platform marks customer as unsubscribed → update CRM"}]]}],["$","p","53",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":""}],["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-semibold text-dark","children":"Architecture:"}],["$","span","2",{"children":"\n1. When a customer is created/updated in CRM, CRM publishes an event\n2. Event goes into a message queue\n3. Worker process consumes event and calls email platform API\n4. If API fails, event stays in queue and retries (with exponential backoff)\n5. When API succeeds, worker logs success to audit trail\n6. Every night, scheduled job verifies that data matches between systems"}]]}],["$","p","54",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":""}],["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-semibold text-dark","children":"Failure scenario:"}],["$","span","2",{"children":" Email platform is down for 20 minutes"}]]}],["$","li","55",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Without this architecture: Customers added during the outage are not subscribed. Issue not discovered for days."}]]}],["$","li","56",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"With this architecture: Events stay in queue. When platform comes back up, all queued events are automatically processed."}]]}],["$","h2","57",{"className":"font-serif text-2xl text-dark mt-12 mb-4","children":"Cost and Timeline"}],["$","p","58",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"For a business with 3-5 system integrations:"}]]}],["$","li","59",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":""}],["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-semibold text-dark","children":"Architecture design:"}],["$","span","2",{"children":" 1 week"}]]}],["$","li","60",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":""}],["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-semibold text-dark","children":"Implementation:"}],["$","span","2",{"children":" 2-3 weeks"}]]}],["$","li","61",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":""}],["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-semibold text-dark","children":"Testing and monitoring setup:"}],["$","span","2",{"children":" 1 week"}]]}],["$","li","62",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":""}],["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-semibold text-dark","children":"Ongoing:"}],["$","span","2",{"children":" 1-2 hours per month per integration"}]]}],["$","p","63",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"The upfront investment saves 10+ hours per month in troubleshooting and manual syncing."}]]}],["$","h2","64",{"className":"font-serif text-2xl text-dark mt-12 mb-4","children":"Red Flags to Watch For"}],["$","li","65",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Integration breaks after the other platform updates their API"}]]}],["$","li","66",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"You have no visibility into whether data is syncing correctly"}]]}],["$","li","67",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Downstream processes fail silently"}]]}],["$","li","68",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"You are polling for data instead of using webhooks"}]]}],["$","li","69",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Integration is a one-way data dump"}]]}],["$","p","70",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Any of these is a sign the integration needs to be rebuilt."}]]}],["$","h2","71",{"className":"font-serif text-2xl text-dark mt-12 mb-4","children":"The Bottom Line"}],["$","p","72",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"The best systems are not tightly coupled. They are loosely coupled, with clear interfaces, graceful failure handling, and 